181 // When the MDNode can be part of the type system, the DIE can be shared ----

477 ----
478 void DwarfUnit::addConstantValue(DIE &Die, const APInt &Val, bool Unsigned) { 0
479 unsigned CIBitWidth = Val.getBitWidth(); 0
480 if (CIBitWidth <= 64) { 0
481 addConstantValue(Die, Unsigned, 0
482 Unsigned ? Val.getZExtValue() : Val.getSExtValue()); 0
483 return; 0
484 } ----
485 ----
486 DIEBlock *Block = new (DIEValueAllocator) DIEBlock; 0
487 ----
488 // Get the raw data form of the large APInt. ----
489 const uint64_t *Ptr64 = Val.getRawData(); 0
490 ----
491 int NumBytes = Val.getBitWidth() / 8; // 8 bits per byte. 0
492 bool LittleEndian = Asm->getDataLayout().isLittleEndian(); 0
493 ----
494 // Output the constant to DWARF one byte at a time. ----
495 for (int i = 0; i < NumBytes; i++) { 0
496 uint8_t c; ----
497 if (LittleEndian) 0
498 c = Ptr64[i / 8] >> (8 * (i & 7)); 0
499 else ----
500 c = Ptr64[(NumBytes - 1 - i) / 8] >> (8 * ((NumBytes - 1 - i) & 7)); 0
501 addUInt(*Block, dwarf::DW_FORM_data1, c); 0
502 } ----
503 ----
504 addBlock(Die, dwarf::DW_AT_const_value, Block); 0
505 } ----

641 } ----

643 DD->addAccelType(*CUNode, Ty->getName(), TyDIE, Flags); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

657 std::string DwarfUnit::getParentContextString(const DIScope *Context) const { 0
658 if (!Context) 0
659 return ""; 0
660 ----
661 // FIXME: Decide whether to implement this for non-C++ languages. ----
662 if (!dwarf::isCPlusPlus((dwarf::SourceLanguage)getLanguage())) 0
663 return ""; 0
664 ----
665 std::string CS; 0
666 SmallVector Parents; 0
667 while (!isa(Context)) { 0
668 Parents.push_back(Context); 0
669 if (const DIScope *S = Context->getScope()) 0
670 Context = S; 0
671 else ----
672 // Structure, etc types will have a NULL context if they're at the top ----
673 // level. ----
674 break; 0
675 } ----
676 ----
677 // Reverse iterate over our list to go from the outermost construct to the ----
678 // innermost. ----
679 for (const DIScope *Ctx : llvm::reverse(Parents)) { 0
680 StringRef Name = Ctx->getName(); 0
681 if (Name.empty() && isa(Ctx)) 0
682 Name = "(anonymous namespace)"; 0
683 if (!Name.empty()) { 0
684 CS += Name; 0
685 CS += "::"; 0
686 } ----
687 } ----
688 return CS; 0
689 } 0

691 void DwarfUnit::constructTypeDIE(DIE &Buffer, const DIBasicType *BTy) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
692 // Get core information. ----
693 StringRef Name = BTy->getName(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
694 // Add name if not anonymous or intermediate type. ----
695 if (!Name.empty()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
696 addString(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_name, Name); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
697 ----
698 // An unspecified type only has a name attribute. ----
699 if (BTy->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_unspecified_type) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
700 return; 0
701 ----
702 if (BTy->getTag() != dwarf::DW_TAG_string_type) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
703 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_encoding, dwarf::DW_FORM_data1, 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
704 BTy->getEncoding()); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
705 ----
706 uint64_t Size = BTy->getSizeInBits() >> 3; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
707 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_byte_size, std::nullopt, Size); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
708 ----
709 if (BTy->isBigEndian()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
710 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_endianity, std::nullopt, dwarf::DW_END_big); 0
711 else if (BTy->isLittleEndian()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
712 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_endianity, std::nullopt, dwarf::DW_END_little); 0
713 } ----

715 void DwarfUnit::constructTypeDIE(DIE &Buffer, const DIStringType *STy) { 0
716 // Get core information. ----
717 StringRef Name = STy->getName(); 0
718 // Add name if not anonymous or intermediate type. ----
719 if (!Name.empty()) 0
720 addString(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_name, Name); 0
721 ----
722 if (DIVariable *Var = STy->getStringLength()) { 0
723 if (auto *VarDIE = getDIE(Var)) 0
724 addDIEEntry(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_string_length, *VarDIE); 0
725 } else if (DIExpression *Expr = STy->getStringLengthExp()) { 0
726 DIELoc *Loc = new (DIEValueAllocator) DIELoc; 0
727 DIEDwarfExpression DwarfExpr(*Asm, getCU(), *Loc); 0
728 // This is to describe the memory location of the ----
729 // length of a Fortran deferred length string, so ----
730 // lock it down as such. ----
731 DwarfExpr.setMemoryLocationKind(); 0
732 DwarfExpr.addExpression(Expr); 0
733 addBlock(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_string_length, DwarfExpr.finalize()); 0
734 } else { 0
735 uint64_t Size = STy->getSizeInBits() >> 3; 0
736 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_byte_size, std::nullopt, Size); 0
737 } ----
738 ----
739 if (DIExpression *Expr = STy->getStringLocationExp()) { 0
740 DIELoc *Loc = new (DIEValueAllocator) DIELoc; 0
741 DIEDwarfExpression DwarfExpr(*Asm, getCU(), *Loc); 0
742 // This is to describe the memory location of the ----
743 // string, so lock it down as such. ----
744 DwarfExpr.setMemoryLocationKind(); 0
745 DwarfExpr.addExpression(Expr); 0
746 addBlock(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_data_location, DwarfExpr.finalize()); 0
747 } 0
748 ----
749 if (STy->getEncoding()) { 0
750 // For eventual Unicode support. ----
751 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_encoding, dwarf::DW_FORM_data1, 0
752 STy->getEncoding()); 0
753 } ----
754 } 0
755 ----
756 void DwarfUnit::constructTypeDIE(DIE &Buffer, const DIDerivedType *DTy) { 0
757 // Get core information. ----
758 StringRef Name = DTy->getName(); 0
759 uint64_t Size = DTy->getSizeInBits() >> 3; 0
760 uint16_t Tag = Buffer.getTag(); 0
761 ----
762 // Map to main type, void will not have a type. ----
763 const DIType *FromTy = DTy->getBaseType(); 0
764 if (FromTy) 0
765 addType(Buffer, FromTy); 0
766 ----
767 // Add name if not anonymous or intermediate type. ----
768 if (!Name.empty()) 0
769 addString(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_name, Name); 0
770 ----
771 addAnnotation(Buffer, DTy->getAnnotations()); 0
772 ----
773 // If alignment is specified for a typedef , create and insert DW_AT_alignment ----
774 // attribute in DW_TAG_typedef DIE. ----
775 if (Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_typedef && DD->getDwarfVersion() >= 5) { 0
776 uint32_t AlignInBytes = DTy->getAlignInBytes(); 0
777 if (AlignInBytes > 0) 0
778 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_alignment, dwarf::DW_FORM_udata, 0
779 AlignInBytes); ----
780 } ----
781 ----
782 // Add size if non-zero (derived types might be zero-sized.) ----
783 if (Size && Tag != dwarf::DW_TAG_pointer_type 0
784 && Tag != dwarf::DW_TAG_ptr_to_member_type 0
785 && Tag != dwarf::DW_TAG_reference_type 0
786 && Tag != dwarf::DW_TAG_rvalue_reference_type) 0
787 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_byte_size, std::nullopt, Size); 0
788 ----
789 if (Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_ptr_to_member_type) 0
790 addDIEEntry(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_containing_type, 0
791 *getOrCreateTypeDIE(cast(DTy)->getClassType())); 0
792 ----
793 addAccess(Buffer, DTy->getFlags()); 0
794 ----
795 // Add source line info if available and TyDesc is not a forward declaration. ----
796 if (!DTy->isForwardDecl()) 0
797 addSourceLine(Buffer, DTy); 0
798 ----
799 // If DWARF address space value is other than None, add it. The IR ----
800 // verifier checks that DWARF address space only exists for pointer ----
801 // or reference types. ----
802 if (DTy->getDWARFAddressSpace()) 0
803 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_address_class, dwarf::DW_FORM_data4, 0
804 *DTy->getDWARFAddressSpace()); 0
805 } 0
806 ----
807 void DwarfUnit::constructSubprogramArguments(DIE &Buffer, DITypeRefArray Args) { 0
808 for (unsigned i = 1, N = Args.size(); i < N; ++i) { 0
809 const DIType *Ty = Args[i]; 0
810 if (!Ty) { 0
811 assert(i == N-1 && "Unspecified parameter must be the last argument"); 0
812 createAndAddDIE(dwarf::DW_TAG_unspecified_parameters, Buffer); 0
813 } else { ----
814 DIE &Arg = createAndAddDIE(dwarf::DW_TAG_formal_parameter, Buffer); 0
815 addType(Arg, Ty); 0
816 if (Ty->isArtificial()) 0
817 addFlag(Arg, dwarf::DW_AT_artificial); 0
818 } ----
819 } ----
820 } 0
821 ----
822 void DwarfUnit::constructTypeDIE(DIE &Buffer, const DISubroutineType *CTy) { 0
823 // Add return type. A void return won't have a type. ----
824 auto Elements = cast(CTy)->getTypeArray(); 0
825 if (Elements.size()) 0
826 if (auto RTy = Elements[0]) 0
827 addType(Buffer, RTy); 0
828 ----
829 bool isPrototyped = true; 0
830 if (Elements.size() == 2 && !Elements[1]) 0
831 isPrototyped = false; 0
832 ----
833 constructSubprogramArguments(Buffer, Elements); 0
834 ----
835 // Add prototype flag if we're dealing with a C language and the function has ----
836 // been prototyped. ----
837 if (isPrototyped && dwarf::isC((dwarf::SourceLanguage)getLanguage())) 0
838 addFlag(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_prototyped); 0
839 ----
840 // Add a DW_AT_calling_convention if this has an explicit convention. ----
841 if (CTy->getCC() && CTy->getCC() != dwarf::DW_CC_normal) 0
842 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_calling_convention, dwarf::DW_FORM_data1, 0
843 CTy->getCC()); 0
844 ----
845 if (CTy->isLValueReference()) 0
846 addFlag(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_reference); 0
847 ----
848 if (CTy->isRValueReference()) 0
849 addFlag(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_rvalue_reference); 0
850 } 0

852 void DwarfUnit::addAnnotation(DIE &Buffer, DINodeArray Annotations) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
853 if (!Annotations) 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
854 return; 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
855 ----
856 for (const Metadata *Annotation : Annotations->operands()) { 0
857 const MDNode *MD = cast(Annotation); 0
858 const MDString *Name = cast(MD->getOperand(0)); 0
859 const auto &Value = MD->getOperand(1); 0
860 ----
861 DIE &AnnotationDie = createAndAddDIE(dwarf::DW_TAG_LLVM_annotation, Buffer); 0
862 addString(AnnotationDie, dwarf::DW_AT_name, Name->getString()); 0
863 if (const auto *Data = dyn_cast(Value)) 0
864 addString(AnnotationDie, dwarf::DW_AT_const_value, Data->getString()); 0
865 else if (const auto *Data = dyn_cast(Value)) 0
866 addConstantValue(AnnotationDie, Data->getValue()->getUniqueInteger(), 0
867 /*Unsigned=*/true); ----
868 else ----
869 assert(false && "Unsupported annotation value type"); 0
870 } ----
871 } ----
872 ----
873 void DwarfUnit::constructTypeDIE(DIE &Buffer, const DICompositeType *CTy) { 0
874 // Add name if not anonymous or intermediate type. ----
875 StringRef Name = CTy->getName(); 0
876 ----
877 uint64_t Size = CTy->getSizeInBits() >> 3; 0
878 uint16_t Tag = Buffer.getTag(); 0
879 ----
880 switch (Tag) { 0
881 case dwarf::DW_TAG_array_type: 0
882 constructArrayTypeDIE(Buffer, CTy); 0
883 break; 0
884 case dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type: 0
885 constructEnumTypeDIE(Buffer, CTy); 0
886 break; 0
887 case dwarf::DW_TAG_variant_part: 0
888 case dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type: ----
889 case dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type: ----
890 case dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type: ----
891 case dwarf::DW_TAG_namelist: { ----
892 // Emit the discriminator for a variant part. ----
893 DIDerivedType *Discriminator = nullptr; 0
894 if (Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_variant_part) { 0
895 Discriminator = CTy->getDiscriminator(); 0
896 if (Discriminator) { 0
897 // DWARF says: ----
898 // If the variant part has a discriminant, the discriminant is ----
899 // represented by a separate debugging information entry which is ----
900 // a child of the variant part entry. ----
901 DIE &DiscMember = constructMemberDIE(Buffer, Discriminator); 0
902 addDIEEntry(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_discr, DiscMember); 0
903 } ----
904 } ----
905 ----
906 // Add template parameters to a class, structure or union types. ----
907 if (Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type || 0
908 Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type || Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type) 0
909 addTemplateParams(Buffer, CTy->getTemplateParams()); 0
910 ----
911 // Add elements to structure type. ----
912 DINodeArray Elements = CTy->getElements(); 0
913 for (const auto *Element : Elements) { 0
914 if (!Element) 0
915 continue; 0
916 if (auto *SP = dyn_cast(Element)) 0
917 getOrCreateSubprogramDIE(SP); 0
918 else if (auto *DDTy = dyn_cast(Element)) { 0
919 if (DDTy->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_friend) { 0
920 DIE &ElemDie = createAndAddDIE(dwarf::DW_TAG_friend, Buffer); 0
921 addType(ElemDie, DDTy->getBaseType(), dwarf::DW_AT_friend); 0
922 } else if (DDTy->isStaticMember()) { 0
923 getOrCreateStaticMemberDIE(DDTy); 0
924 } else if (Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_variant_part) { 0
925 // When emitting a variant part, wrap each member in ----
926 // DW_TAG_variant. ----
927 DIE &Variant = createAndAddDIE(dwarf::DW_TAG_variant, Buffer); 0
928 if (const ConstantInt *CI = 0
929 dyn_cast_or_null(DDTy->getDiscriminantValue())) { 0
930 if (DD->isUnsignedDIType(Discriminator->getBaseType())) 0
931 addUInt(Variant, dwarf::DW_AT_discr_value, std::nullopt, 0
932 CI->getZExtValue()); ----
933 else ----
934 addSInt(Variant, dwarf::DW_AT_discr_value, std::nullopt, 0
935 CI->getSExtValue()); ----
936 } ----
937 constructMemberDIE(Variant, DDTy); 0
938 } else { ----
939 constructMemberDIE(Buffer, DDTy); 0
940 } ----
941 } else if (auto *Property = dyn_cast(Element)) { 0
942 DIE &ElemDie = createAndAddDIE(Property->getTag(), Buffer); 0
943 StringRef PropertyName = Property->getName(); 0
944 addString(ElemDie, dwarf::DW_AT_APPLE_property_name, PropertyName); 0
945 if (Property->getType()) 0
946 addType(ElemDie, Property->getType()); 0
947 addSourceLine(ElemDie, Property); 0
948 StringRef GetterName = Property->getGetterName(); 0
949 if (!GetterName.empty()) 0
950 addString(ElemDie, dwarf::DW_AT_APPLE_property_getter, GetterName); 0
951 StringRef SetterName = Property->getSetterName(); 0
952 if (!SetterName.empty()) 0
953 addString(ElemDie, dwarf::DW_AT_APPLE_property_setter, SetterName); 0
954 if (unsigned PropertyAttributes = Property->getAttributes()) 0
955 addUInt(ElemDie, dwarf::DW_AT_APPLE_property_attribute, std::nullopt, 0
956 PropertyAttributes); ----
957 } else if (auto *Composite = dyn_cast(Element)) { 0
958 if (Composite->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_variant_part) { 0
959 DIE &VariantPart = createAndAddDIE(Composite->getTag(), Buffer); 0
960 constructTypeDIE(VariantPart, Composite); 0
961 } ----
962 } else if (Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_namelist) { 0
963 auto *Var = dyn_cast(Element); 0
964 auto *VarDIE = getDIE(Var); 0
965 if (VarDIE) { 0
966 DIE &ItemDie = createAndAddDIE(dwarf::DW_TAG_namelist_item, Buffer); 0
967 addDIEEntry(ItemDie, dwarf::DW_AT_namelist_item, *VarDIE); 0
968 } ----
969 } ----
970 } ----
971 ----
972 if (CTy->isAppleBlockExtension()) 0
973 addFlag(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_APPLE_block); 0
974 ----
975 if (CTy->getExportSymbols()) 0
976 addFlag(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_export_symbols); 0
977 ----
978 // This is outside the DWARF spec, but GDB expects a DW_AT_containing_type ----
979 // inside C++ composite types to point to the base class with the vtable. ----
980 // Rust uses DW_AT_containing_type to link a vtable to the type ----
981 // for which it was created. ----
982 if (auto *ContainingType = CTy->getVTableHolder()) 0
983 addDIEEntry(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_containing_type, 0
984 *getOrCreateTypeDIE(ContainingType)); 0
985 ----
986 if (CTy->isObjcClassComplete()) 0
987 addFlag(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_APPLE_objc_complete_type); 0
988 ----
989 // Add the type's non-standard calling convention. ----
990 // DW_CC_pass_by_value/DW_CC_pass_by_reference are introduced in DWARF 5. ----
991 if (!Asm->TM.Options.DebugStrictDwarf || DD->getDwarfVersion() >= 5) { 0
992 uint8_t CC = 0; 0
993 if (CTy->isTypePassByValue()) 0
994 CC = dwarf::DW_CC_pass_by_value; 0
995 else if (CTy->isTypePassByReference()) 0
996 CC = dwarf::DW_CC_pass_by_reference; 0
997 if (CC) 0
998 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_calling_convention, dwarf::DW_FORM_data1, 0
999 CC); ----
1000 } ----
1001 break; 0
1002 } ----
1003 default: 0
1004 break; 0
1005 } ----
1006 ----
1007 // Add name if not anonymous or intermediate type. ----
1008 if (!Name.empty()) 0
1009 addString(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_name, Name); 0
1010 ----
1011 addAnnotation(Buffer, CTy->getAnnotations()); 0
1012 ----
1013 if (Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type || 0
1014 Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type || Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type || 0
1015 Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type) { ----
1016 // Add size if non-zero (derived types might be zero-sized.) ----
1017 // Ignore the size if it's a non-enum forward decl. ----
1018 // TODO: Do we care about size for enum forward declarations? ----
1019 if (Size && 0
1020 (!CTy->isForwardDecl() || Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type)) 0
1021 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_byte_size, std::nullopt, Size); 0
1022 else if (!CTy->isForwardDecl()) 0
1023 // Add zero size if it is not a forward declaration. ----
1024 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_byte_size, std::nullopt, 0); 0
1025 ----
1026 // If we're a forward decl, say so. ----
1027 if (CTy->isForwardDecl()) 0
1028 addFlag(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_declaration); 0
1029 ----
1030 // Add accessibility info if available. ----
1031 addAccess(Buffer, CTy->getFlags()); 0
1032 ----
1033 // Add source line info if available. ----
1034 if (!CTy->isForwardDecl()) 0
1035 addSourceLine(Buffer, CTy); 0
1036 ----
1037 // No harm in adding the runtime language to the declaration. ----
1038 unsigned RLang = CTy->getRuntimeLang(); 0
1039 if (RLang) 0
1040 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_APPLE_runtime_class, dwarf::DW_FORM_data1, 0
1041 RLang); ----
1042 ----
1043 // Add align info if available. ----
1044 if (uint32_t AlignInBytes = CTy->getAlignInBytes()) 0
1045 addUInt(Buffer, dwarf::DW_AT_alignment, dwarf::DW_FORM_udata, 0
1046 AlignInBytes); ----
1047 } ----
1048 } 0

1063 void DwarfUnit::constructTemplateValueParameterDIE( 0
1064 DIE &Buffer, const DITemplateValueParameter *VP) { ----
1065 DIE &ParamDIE = createAndAddDIE(VP->getTag(), Buffer); 0
1066 ----
1067 // Add the type if there is one, template template and template parameter ----
1068 // packs will not have a type. ----
1069 if (VP->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_template_value_parameter) 0
1070 addType(ParamDIE, VP->getType()); 0
1071 if (!VP->getName().empty()) 0
1072 addString(ParamDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_name, VP->getName()); 0
1073 if (VP->isDefault() && isCompatibleWithVersion(5)) 0
1074 addFlag(ParamDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_default_value); 0
1075 if (Metadata *Val = VP->getValue()) { 0
1076 if (ConstantInt *CI = mdconst::dyn_extract(Val)) 0
1077 addConstantValue(ParamDIE, CI, VP->getType()); 0
1078 else if (GlobalValue *GV = mdconst::dyn_extract(Val)) { 0
1079 // We cannot describe the location of dllimport'd entities: the ----
1080 // computation of their address requires loads from the IAT. ----
1081 if (!GV->hasDLLImportStorageClass()) { 0
1082 // For declaration non-type template parameters (such as global values ----
1083 // and functions) ----
1084 DIELoc *Loc = new (DIEValueAllocator) DIELoc; 0
1085 addOpAddress(*Loc, Asm->getSymbol(GV)); 0
1086 // Emit DW_OP_stack_value to use the address as the immediate value of ----
1087 // the parameter, rather than a pointer to it. ----
1088 addUInt(*Loc, dwarf::DW_FORM_data1, dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value); 0
1089 addBlock(ParamDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_location, Loc); 0
1090 } ----
1091 } else if (VP->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_GNU_template_template_param) { 0
1092 assert(isa(Val)); 0
1093 addString(ParamDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_GNU_template_name, 0
1094 cast(Val)->getString()); ----
1095 } else if (VP->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_GNU_template_parameter_pack) { 0
1096 addTemplateParams(ParamDIE, cast(Val)); 0
1097 } ----
1098 } ----

1352 void DwarfUnit::constructSubrangeDIE(DIE &Buffer, const DISubrange *SR, 0
1353 DIE *IndexTy) { ----
1354 DIE &DW_Subrange = createAndAddDIE(dwarf::DW_TAG_subrange_type, Buffer); 0
1355 addDIEEntry(DW_Subrange, dwarf::DW_AT_type, *IndexTy); 0
1356 ----
1357 // The LowerBound value defines the lower bounds which is typically zero for ----
1358 // C/C++. The Count value is the number of elements. Values are 64 bit. If ----
1359 // Count == -1 then the array is unbounded and we do not emit ----
1360 // DW_AT_lower_bound and DW_AT_count attributes. ----
1361 int64_t DefaultLowerBound = getDefaultLowerBound(); 0
1362 ----
1363 auto AddBoundTypeEntry = [&](dwarf::Attribute Attr, 0
1364 DISubrange::BoundType Bound) -> void { ----
1365 if (auto *BV = dyn_cast_if_present(Bound)) { 0
1366 if (auto *VarDIE = getDIE(BV)) 0
1367 addDIEEntry(DW_Subrange, Attr, *VarDIE); 0
1368 } else if (auto *BE = dyn_cast_if_present(Bound)) { 0
1369 DIELoc *Loc = new (DIEValueAllocator) DIELoc; 0
1370 DIEDwarfExpression DwarfExpr(*Asm, getCU(), *Loc); 0
1371 DwarfExpr.setMemoryLocationKind(); 0
1372 DwarfExpr.addExpression(BE); 0
1373 addBlock(DW_Subrange, Attr, DwarfExpr.finalize()); 0
1374 } else if (auto *BI = dyn_cast_if_present(Bound)) { 0
1375 if (Attr == dwarf::DW_AT_count) { 0
1376 if (BI->getSExtValue() != -1) 0
1377 addUInt(DW_Subrange, Attr, std::nullopt, BI->getSExtValue()); 0
1378 } else if (Attr != dwarf::DW_AT_lower_bound || DefaultLowerBound == -1 || 0
1379 BI->getSExtValue() != DefaultLowerBound) 0
1380 addSInt(DW_Subrange, Attr, dwarf::DW_FORM_sdata, BI->getSExtValue()); 0
1381 } ----
1382 }; 0
1383 ----
1384 AddBoundTypeEntry(dwarf::DW_AT_lower_bound, SR->getLowerBound()); 0
1385 ----
1386 AddBoundTypeEntry(dwarf::DW_AT_count, SR->getCount()); 0
1387 ----
1388 AddBoundTypeEntry(dwarf::DW_AT_upper_bound, SR->getUpperBound()); 0
1389 ----
1390 AddBoundTypeEntry(dwarf::DW_AT_byte_stride, SR->getStride()); 0
1391 } 0

1400 int64_t DefaultLowerBound = getDefaultLowerBound(); 0
1401 ----
1402 auto AddBoundTypeEntry = [&](dwarf::Attribute Attr, 0
1403 DIGenericSubrange::BoundType Bound) -> void { ----
1404 if (auto *BV = dyn_cast_if_present(Bound)) { 0
1405 if (auto *VarDIE = getDIE(BV)) 0
1406 addDIEEntry(DwGenericSubrange, Attr, *VarDIE); 0
1407 } else if (auto *BE = dyn_cast_if_present(Bound)) { 0
1408 if (BE->isConstant() && 0
1409 DIExpression::SignedOrUnsignedConstant::SignedConstant == ----

1411 if (Attr != dwarf::DW_AT_lower_bound || DefaultLowerBound == -1 || 0
1412 static_cast(BE->getElement(1)) != DefaultLowerBound) 0

1414 BE->getElement(1)); 0
1415 } else { ----
1416 DIELoc *Loc = new (DIEValueAllocator) DIELoc; 0

1419 DwarfExpr.addExpression(BE); 0

1421 } 0
1422 } ----
1423 }; 0
1424 ----
1425 AddBoundTypeEntry(dwarf::DW_AT_lower_bound, GSR->getLowerBound()); 0
1426 AddBoundTypeEntry(dwarf::DW_AT_count, GSR->getCount()); 0
1427 AddBoundTypeEntry(dwarf::DW_AT_upper_bound, GSR->getUpperBound()); 0

1445 ----
1446 /// Returns true if the vector's size differs from the sum of sizes of elements ----
1447 /// the user specified. This can occur if the vector has been rounded up to ----
1448 /// fit memory alignment constraints. ----
1449 static bool hasVectorBeenPadded(const DICompositeType *CTy) { 0
1450 assert(CTy && CTy->isVector() && "Composite type is not a vector"); 0
1451 const uint64_t ActualSize = CTy->getSizeInBits(); 0
1452 ----
1453 // Obtain the size of each element in the vector. ----
1454 DIType *BaseTy = CTy->getBaseType(); 0
1455 assert(BaseTy && "Unknown vector element type."); 0
1456 const uint64_t ElementSize = BaseTy->getSizeInBits(); 0
1457 ----
1458 // Locate the number of elements in the vector. ----
1459 const DINodeArray Elements = CTy->getElements(); 0
1460 assert(Elements.size() == 1 && 0
1461 Elements[0]->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_subrange_type && ----
1462 "Invalid vector element array, expected one element of type subrange"); ----
1463 const auto Subrange = cast(Elements[0]); 0
1464 const auto NumVecElements = ----
1465 Subrange->getCount() 0
1466 ? cast(Subrange->getCount())->getSExtValue() 0
1467 : 0; 0
1468 ----
1469 // Ensure we found the element count and that the actual size is wide ----
1470 // enough to contain the requested size. ----
1471 assert(ActualSize >= (NumVecElements * ElementSize) && "Invalid vector size"); 0
1472 return ActualSize != (NumVecElements * ElementSize); 0
1473 } ----
1474 ----

1591 DIE &DwarfUnit::constructMemberDIE(DIE &Buffer, const DIDerivedType *DT) { 0

1636 // which can't be done with bitfields. Thus we use FieldSize here. ----
1637 uint32_t AlignInBits = FieldSize; 0
1638 uint32_t AlignMask = ~(AlignInBits - 1); 0
1639 // The bits from the start of the storage unit to the start of the field. ----
1640 uint64_t StartBitOffset = Offset - (Offset & AlignMask); 0
1641 // The byte offset of the field's aligned storage unit inside the struct. ----
1642 OffsetInBytes = (Offset - StartBitOffset) / 8; 0
1643 ----

1646 uint64_t FieldOffset = (HiMark - FieldSize); 0

1651 Offset = FieldSize - (Offset + Size); 0
1652 ----

1654 OffsetInBytes = FieldOffset >> 3; 0

1656 addUInt(MemberDie, dwarf::DW_AT_data_bit_offset, std::nullopt, Offset); 0
1657 } ----
